<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1441,262,511]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,262,286]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[556,781,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[556,621,262,286]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Viola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[628,781,263,287]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, distant from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1888" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1888" box="[951,1278,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pachyneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1105,262,286]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Pachyneuria</emphasis>
Mabille, 1888
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1293,1347,263,287]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1888" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1888" box="[192,624,294,319]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pachyneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[192,448,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Pachyneuria obscura</emphasis>
Mabille, 1888
</taxonomicName>
), where species of this genus were formerly placed (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1328,295,319]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[192,275,1906,1928]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,780,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[192,1440,779,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Genomic trees of Carcharodini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677243/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Keys to E. 
<quantity box="[215,302,327,351]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2578" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="20.7">20.7 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[309,473,327,351]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1888" box="[640,794,326,350]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pachyneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,794,326,350]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Pachyneuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of long tufts of scales near hindwing costa above in males and swollen hindwing vein Sc+R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[839,848,374,388]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">1</subScript>
, similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[984,1049,358,382]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[984,1049,358,382]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Viola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, [1819]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1107,1435,358,383]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Nisoniades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1107,1242,358,382]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Nisoniades</emphasis>
H√ºbner, [1819]
</taxonomicName>
, among others. Differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[512,577,390,414]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[512,577,390,414]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Viola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other genera in genitalia and diagnosed by asymmetric uncus with asymmetric processes, reduced harpe of the right valva compared to the expanded rounded ampulla. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly1222.46.1:A28C, aly207.4.6:C1025G, aly 
<date box="[228,335,487,511]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" value="1019-07-07">1019.7.7</date>
:T59A, aly 
<date box="[457,567,487,511]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" value="2012-07-07">2012.7.7</date>
:C98G, aly638.27.5:T694A.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,532,556]" box="[192,1440,532,556]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,342,532,556]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, a fusion of 
<emphasis box="[1132,1159,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Vi</emphasis>
[ola] and [Pachyne] 
<emphasis box="[1382,1432,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">uria</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,577,602]" box="[192,1440,577,602]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,422,577,601]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[478,529,578,602]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1953" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1953" box="[629,986,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pachyneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lista">
<emphasis box="[629,835,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Pachyneuria lista</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[840,986,577,601]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1940" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1940" box="[1045,1435,577,602]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pellicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herophile">
<emphasis box="[1045,1248,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Pellicia herophile</emphasis>
Hayward, 1940
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,787,623,647]" box="[192,787,623,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,623,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Verity, 1940" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1940" box="[460,784,623,647]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Carcharodini">Carcharodini Verity, 1940</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
